  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/2302.06360v1</id>
    <title>Review on Efficient Strategies for Coordinated Motion and Tracking in Swarm Robotics</title>
    <updated>2023-02-13T13:46:21Z</updated>
    <link href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2302.06360v1" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/>
    <link href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2302.06360v1" rel="related" type="application/pdf" title="pdf"/>
    <summary>Swarm robotics is a creative method of organizing multi-robot structures, consisting of many basic robots influenced by communal insects. The greatest astonishing attribute of swarm robots is their capacity to function together to accomplish a collective objective. This paper addresses the list of current surveys, problems and algorithms that were stimulated in the research of Coordinated Movement in Swarm robotics. Algorithms for swarm robotics movement are contrasted, considering the swarm micro-robots to accomplish aggregation, creation, and clamouring by contrasting the relative computational simulations between the algorithms and simulations used.</summary>
    <category term="cs.RO" scheme="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom"/>
    <published>2023-02-13T13:46:21Z</published>
    <arxiv:comment>This is an outcome of a literature review which has yet to be published</arxiv:comment>
